19. Bg3 f5 20. Nd2 e5 21. dxe5 (21. Bh2 f4 22. O-O fxe3 23. fxe3 exd4 24. exd4
Nxd4 25. Rxf8+ Rxf8 26. cxd4 Qxd4+ 27. Kh1 Qb2 28. Bxc4+ bxc4 29. Nxc4 Qf2 $14)
21... Nxe5 (21... f4 22. exf4 gxf4 23. Bh4 $11) 22. Bxe5 $11 Qxe5 {Black has
the pair of bishops} 23. Nf3 {White threatens to win material: Nf3xe5} Qe4 (
23... Qf6 24. Qd5+ Kh7 25. O-O $11) 24. O-O {White castles and improves king
safety} (24. Nd4 Rae8 25. Bf3 Qe5 $14) 24... Rac8 (24... f4 $5 {should be
examined more closely} 25. Nd4 fxe3 $11) 25. Nd4 $16 Bxd4 (25... f4 26. Bf3 Qd3
27. Ne6 $16) 26. cxd4 {White has a new protected passed pawn: d4. Black has a
new protected passed pawn: c4} (26. Qxd4 $5 f4 27. Bf3 Qxd4 28. exd4 $16) 26...
f4 $14 {Black threatens to win material: f4xe3} 27. Bf3 Qd3 28. Qxd3 Bxd3 {
Black can be proud of that piece} 29. Rfe1 fxe3 30. fxe3 {White has a new
passed pawn: e3.} Kg7 (30... Rcd8 31. d5 $14) 31. Rc3 (31. e4 Rf4 $16) 31...
