has a cramped position} Qb6 17. Ra4 (17. b5 axb5 18. Ra5 b4 $15) 17... Qc6 {
Black threatens to win material: Qc6xa4} (17... Nc6 18. Raa1 $17) 18. Ra3 Qc4
19. Ng5 $2 (19. Qxc4 $142 Rxc4 20. Rc3 $17) 19... Qxd3 $19 20. Rxd3 Nc6 (20...
Rc2 $5 21. Nf3 Rxb2 22. Bc1 $19) 21. f4 Bxb4 22. f5 Bxd2 23. Rxd2 exf5 24. Rxf5
h6 25. Nf3 Nd8 26. h3 (26. Nh4 Ne6 $17) 26... Ne6 $19 27. Rd3 (27. Ne1 $19)
27... Rc2 28. Rb3 b5 29. Kh2 (29. Rh5 Rfc8 30. Rh4 R8c4 $19) 29... Rb8 (29...
Rfc8 {makes it even easier for Black} 30. Ra3 R8c6 31. b3 $19) 30. h4 (30. Ra3
Ra8 31. Rb3 Rac8 $19) 30... a5 {[%cal Yb5b4] Black plans b4} 31. Kh3 (31. Ra3 {
is the last straw} a4 32. Ra2 $19) 31... b4 32. g4 (32. Ne1 {desperation} Re2
33. Rg3 Rxe1 34. Rff3 $19) 32... a4 33. Rd3 a3 34. bxa3 b3 35. g5 (35. Nd2 {
otherwise it's curtains at once} b2 36. Rf1 Nf4+ 37. Rxf4 Rxd2 38. Rxd2 $19)
35... hxg5 (35... b2 36. Rd1 Rc1 37. gxh6 b1=Q 38. h7+ Kxh7 39. Rh5+ Kg8 40.
