{[%mdl 8192] A00: Irregular Openings} 1. a4 e5 2. e4 Nf6 3. Nc3 Bc5 $146 (3...
Bb4 4. Bc4 O-O 5. d3 d5 6. exd5 c6 7. dxc6 Nxc6 8. Nf3 Bg4 9. h3 Bxf3 10. Qxf3
Nd4 11. Qd1 {1/2-1/2 (11) Nirav Y,R (2255)-Suvrajit,S (2205) Kolkata 1996}) (
3... Nc6 4. Nf3 Bb4 5. Bb5 O-O 6. O-O d6 7. d3 Bg4 8. Ne2 a6 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10.
Ng3 Nh5 11. h3 Nxg3 12. fxg3 Bd7 13. g4 Bc5+ 14. Kh1 Qe7 15. Qe1 f6 16. Nh4 g6
17. Bh6 Rf7 18. Rb1 {Carlsen,M (2837)-Radjabov,T (2788) Astana 2012 1-0 (32)})
4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bb5 d6 6. Bxc6+ bxc6 {Black has the pair of bishops} 7. O-O O-O
8. d3 h6 {Controls g5} 9. Bd2 Bg4 10. Rb1 Rb8 11. h3 Bh5 12. g4 $2 (12. Ne2
Bxf3 13. gxf3 d5 $11) 12... Bg6 $4 {Black has let it slip away} (12... Nxg4
$142 {and the scales tip in favour of Black} 13. Qe1 f5 $19) 13. Ne2 $11 Nh7 $4
{there were better ways to keep up the pressure} (13... a6 $142 $11 {is a
viable option}) 14. b4 $18 Bd4 15. Nexd4 exd4 16. Nxd4 Qd7 17. b5 cxb5 18. Nxb5
(18. axb5 $5 Ra8 19. Ra1 $18) 18... a6 19. Nd4 (19. Nc3 f6 $16) 19... Qxa4 (
19... c5 20. Ne2 $14) 20. Nf5 (20. Rxb8 $5 Rxb8 21. Qa1 Qxa1 22. Rxa1 $16)
20... Bxf5 $14 21. exf5 (21. gxf5 Rxb1 22. Qxb1 Nf6 $14) 21... f6 {Secures g5.}
(21... Rxb1 22. Qxb1 Qc6 23. Qb3 $11) 22. Ra1 {White threatens to win material:
Ra1xa4} Qc6 23. f3 Rb2 24. c3 (24. Rf2 $5 $11 {deserves consideration}) 24...
Ng5 $15 25. Bxg5 hxg5 26. Qc1 Rfb8 27. Qe3 $4 {strolling merrily down the path
to disaster} (27. Rf2 R2b3 $17) 27... Rc2 {Black threatens to win material:
Rc2xc3} (27... Re8 $142 {and the result of the game is clear: Black will win}
28. Rxa6 Qb5 $19) 28. Qe6+ $2 (28. Rac1 $142 Rxc1 29. Rxc1 $17) 28... Kh7 $19
29. Qf7 $4 {simply worsens the situation} (29. Rf2 Qxc3 30. Rxc2 Qxc2 31. Qe1
$19) 29... Rbb2 30. Qg6+ (30. Ra2 {a fruitless try to alter the course of the
game} Rg2+ 31. Kh1 Rxa2 32. Qxa2 Rxa2 33. h4 Qxc3 34. hxg5 Qd2 35. g6+ Kh8 36.
Rf2 Qxf2 37. d4 Qg2#) 30... Kg8 31. Rfb1 (31. Qxg7+ {is no salvation} Kxg7 32.
Rf2 Rxf2 33. Re1 Rg2+ 34. Kh1 Rh2+ 35. Kg1 Rbg2+ 36. Kf1 Qxf3#) 31... Rg2+ (
31... Qb6+ 32. d4 Rxb1+ 33. Rxb1 Qxb1#) 32. Kh1 Rh2+ 33. Kg1 Rbg2+ 34. Kf1
Qxf3+ (34... Qxf3+ 35. Ke1 Rh1#) 0-1

