{[%mdl 8256] E94: King's Indian: Classical: 6 Be2 e5 7 0-0: Various Black 7th
moves} 1. c4 Nf6 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 Bg7 4. Nc3 O-O 5. e4 d6 6. Be2 Nbd7 7. O-O e5
8. d5 Nc5 9. Qc2 a5 10. Be3 b6 11. a3 {White has a very active position} (11.
Nd2 Ne8 12. a3 f5 13. f3 a4 14. Bxc5 bxc5 15. Nxa4 Bh6 16. Nc3 Qh4 17. Rfd1
Be3+ 18. Kh1 Nf6 19. Nf1 Bd4 20. exf5 gxf5 21. Nb5 Rf7 22. Nxd4 cxd4 23. Ng3 f4
24. Ne4 Nxe4 25. fxe4 Rf6 {Heissler,J (2435)-Werner,D (2420) Germany 1997 1-0 
(40)}) 11... Nh5 $146 (11... Ng4 12. Bxc5 bxc5 13. b4 (13. h3 Nh6 14. Qd2 f5
15. Qg5 Qe8 16. Qd2 f4 17. Nb5 Qe7 18. b4 Nf7 19. bxc5 dxc5 20. Rfd1 Nd6 21.
Nxd6 cxd6 22. Rab1 g5 23. Nh2 Qf7 24. Qc3 Kh8 25. Qf3 Bf6 26. Qh5 Qxh5 27. Bxh5
Ba6 {Russell,M (2200)-Aaron,A (2295) London 1978 0-1 (41)}) 13... cxb4 14. axb4
f5 15. Rxa5 Rxa5 16. bxa5 Nf6 17. Nd2 Bh6 18. Bd3 Nh5 19. Nf3 Nf4 20. c5 dxc5
21. a6 Qd6 22. Ra1 c6 23. Bc4 Kh8 24. dxc6 Qxc6 25. Nxe5 Qc7 26. Nf7+ {Csikos,
M (2184)-Kovacs,J (2205) Hungary 2005 1-0}) (11... a4 12. Nd2 Bd7 13. b4 axb3
14. Nxb3 Na4 15. Nb5 h5 16. h3 Nh7 17. Rac1 Bf6 18. Qd2 Bg5 19. f4 exf4 20.
Bxf4 Nc5 21. Nxc5 bxc5 22. Ra1 Bxb5 23. cxb5 Ra4 24. Bd3 Qe7 25. Bc2 Rd4 26.
Qf2 {Vokoun,J (2212)-Novikov,S (2545) Pardubice 2012 0-1 (32)}) 12. b4 Nb7 13.
Bg5 {White threatens to win material: Bg5xd8} f6 {Black threatens to win
material: f6xg5} 14. Bd2 f5 {Black has a cramped position} 15. Bd3 f4 {This
push gains space} (15... Nf4 16. h3 $14) 16. Kh1 (16. h3 Bd7 $14) 16... Bg4 (
16... g5 17. Qd1 $11) 17. Be2 $14 Qd7 {White has an active position} 18. Ng1 (
18. h3 Bxh3 19. bxa5 Nxa5 20. gxh3 Qxh3+ 21. Kg1 $11) 18... Bxe2 $11 {Black
forks: f1+c4} 19. Ncxe2 Rf7 (19... c6 20. Nc3 $11) 20. bxa5 (20. Nf3 Rff8 $14)
20... Nxa5 $11 21. Bxa5 bxa5 (21... Rxa5 22. Nc3 $11) 22. Nf3 h6 {Secures g5} (
22... Rff8 23. Rab1 $14) 23. c5 $14 {Nimzovich: attack the chain at its base}
g5 24. cxd6 (24. h3 g4 25. c6 Qc8 26. hxg4 Qxg4 $14) 24... cxd6 $11 25. Qc6 (
25. Rac1 Rb8 $14) 25... Raf8 $4 {gives the opponent new chances} (25... Qxc6
$142 26. dxc6 Rc7 $17) 26. Qxd7 $14 Rxd7 27. Rac1 (27. Nd2 g4 $14) 27... g4 {
Black threatens to win material: g4xf3} 28. Nh4 f3 (28... Rb8 29. Rc6 $11) 29.
gxf3 $14 gxf3 30. Nc3 (30. Ng3 Nf4 $14) 30... Nf4 (30... Rf4 31. Nf5 $15) 31.
Nf5 {'the knight is the knight!'} Rf6 (31... Rb8 32. Rb1 Rxb1 33. Rxb1 $11) 32.
Rg1 (32. Rce1 Ng2 33. Rb1 Nf4 $14) 32... Nd3 {Black has a mate threat} (32...
Rc7 33. Rb1 $11) 33. Rc2 {Black has a cramped position} (33. Rcf1 Kh7 $14)
33... Kh7 (33... Rc7 34. Rg3 Rxf5 35. exf5 Kf7 $17) 34. Nxg7 $4 {White loses
the upper hand} (34. Nb5 $142 $14 {and White has air to breath}) 34... Rxg7 $17
35. Rxg7+ Kxg7 36. Nd1 Nc5 37. Rc4 (37. Ne3 Nxe4 38. h3 Kg6 $19) 37... Rf4 $19
38. Nc3 Kg6 39. h3 Kh5 40. Kh2 Kh4 41. a4 (41. Nb5 Nxe4 42. Rc2 Kg5 $19) 41...
Rf6 42. Nb5 $4 {White falls apart} (42. Nd1 $142 Kg5 43. Nc3 $19) 42... Rg6 (
42... Nd3 $142 {makes it even easier for Black} 43. Nxd6 Rxd6 $19) 43. Nxd6 (
43. Rc3 Rg2+ 44. Kh1 Rxf2 45. Nxd6 Nxa4 46. Ra3 $19) 43... Nd3 (43... Rg2+ $142
{it becomes clear that Black will call all the shots} 44. Kh1 Nd3 $19) 44. Nf5+
$18 Kh5 45. Ng3+ Kg5 46. Rc2 (46. Rc3 $142 Nxf2 47. Rxf3 $18) 46... Kf4 $4 {
a blunder in a bad position} (46... Rb6 $142 $16) 47. Rd2 (47. Rc6 $142 {
secures the point} Rg8 48. Nh5+ Kg5 49. Nf6 $18) 47... Nxf2 $1 $19 {Remove
defender: f2} 48. d6 (48. Rxf2 Rxg3 {Remove defender}) 48... Rxg3 49. Rxf2 Rg8
50. d7 (50. Rb2 Kxe4 51. d7 Kf4 $19) 50... Kxe4 (50... Rd8 51. Kg1 Rxd7 52. Rf1
Rg7+ 53. Kf2 Rg2+ 54. Ke1 Ra2 55. Rxf3+ Kxf3 56. h4 Rc2 57. Kd1 Rc8 58. Kd2 Kf2
59. Kd3 Ke1 60. h5 Rc7 61. Ke3 Rc3#) 51. Rd2 (51. Rc2 Rd8 52. Kg3 Rxd7 53. Rc3
Rg7+ 54. Kf2 Rg2+ 55. Ke1 $19) 51... Rd8 52. Kg3 Ke3 53. Rd5 (53. Rd6 e4 54.
Kg4 f2 55. Rd1 Rxd7 56. Rxd7 f1=Q 57. Rd5 Qf4+ 58. Kh5 Qf7+ 59. Kxh6 Qxd5 60.
h4 Kd3 61. Kg6 e3 62. h5 Qc6+ 63. Kg5 Qc5+ 64. Kg6 e2 65. h6 Qd5 66. h7 e1=Q
67. h8=Q Qg1+ 68. Kf6 Qgg5#) 53... e4 54. h4 f2 55. Rf5 (55. Rd1 {doesn't
improve anything} Ke2 56. Rb1 Rxd7 57. h5 f1=Q 58. Rxf1 Kxf1 59. Kf4 Re7 60.
Ke3 Re8 61. Kd4 e3 62. Kd5 Rg8 63. Kd4 e2 64. Kc5 e1=Q 65. Kb6 Qe6+ 66. Kc7
Rg7+ 67. Kb8 Qe8#) 55... Rxd7 56. Kg2 (56. Kg4 {does not save the day} Ke2 57.
Kh5 f1=Q 58. Rxf1 Kxf1 59. Kxh6 e3 60. h5 e2 61. Kg6 e1=Q 62. Kf6 Qe7+ 63. Kf5
Rd5+ 64. Kg4 Rg5+ 65. Kh4 Qe5 66. h6 Qg3#) 56... Rd2 (56... Rg7+ 57. Kh3 Ke2
58. Rf4 f1=Q+ 59. Rxf1 Kxf1 60. h5 Kf2 61. Kh4 Kf3 62. Kh3 Rg2 63. Kh4 Rh2#)
57. Rb5 Ke2 58. Rb1 (58. Rf5 {doesn't change the outcome of the game} Ke1 59.
Kg3 e3 60. Rb5 f1=Q 61. Rb1+ Rd1 62. Rb2 e2 63. Rb3 h5 64. Ra3 Qf2+ 65. Kh3 Kf1
66. Rg3 Rd3 67. Rxd3 Qg2#) 58... e3 59. h5 Rd1 60. Rb2+ Kd3 61. Rb3+ (61. Rxf2
{does not improve anything} exf2 62. Kxf2 Rd2+ 63. Kf3 Ra2 64. Kf4 Kd4 65. Kf5
Kd5 66. Kf6 Re2 67. Kf7 Kd6 68. Kf6 Rf2+ 69. Kg6 Ke7 70. Kg7 Rg2+ 71. Kh8 Kf7
72. Kh7 Re2 73. Kh8 Re8+ 74. Kh7 Kf6 75. Kxh6 Rh8#) 61... Kc4 (61... Kc4 62.
Rxe3 f1=Q+ 63. Kg3 Qg1+ 64. Kf3 Rf1+ 65. Ke4 Qh1+ 66. Rf3 Qxf3+ 67. Ke5 Qd5#) (
61... Ke4 62. Kg3 f1=Q 63. Rxe3+ Kxe3 64. Kh4 Qf4+ 65. Kh3 Rh1+ 66. Kg2 Qf3#)
