18. Nxf3 Ndf8 19. Qd5 Qd7 20. Rd2 Qe6 21. Rfd1 Rad8 22. a4 Ne5 23. Nxe5 Bxe5
24. Nb5 Qxd5 {Raupp,T (2275)-Glienke,M (2320) Germany 1986 0-1 (41)}) 10... O-O
11. O-O Nd7 12. Be3 Nf6 13. h3 a6 14. Qb3 Bd6 15. Rfd1 Re8 16. Bf1 h6 17. Rac1
Qe7 18. Re1 Ne5 19. Nd2 c6 20. Bd4 Qc7 21. Nde4 Nxe4 22. Nxe4 Bf8 23. Qg3 Kh8 {
Salanki,E (2265)-Karadzic,B (2330) Budapest 1986 1-0}) 9... Bd7 10. Qb3 Bd6 11.
Nf3 O-O 12. O-O Nh4 13. Be2 Na6 14. Ne4 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Nc5 16. Nxc5 Bxc5 17.
Bf4 Bb6 18. Rac1 Rc8 19. Qc3 Re8 20. Rfe1 Rxe1+ 21. Rxe1 Qf8 22. b4 c6 {
Lizak,P (2401)-Brinovec,D (2201) Pula 2014 1/2-1/2 (57)}) 8... Be7 9. Bd3 O-O {
Black castles and improves king safety} 10. O-O c5 (10... c6 11. Re1 $11) 11.
dxc5 Bxc5 12. Ne4 (12. Ng5 Nd7 $16) 12... Nd7 (12... Bb6 13. b3 Qd7 14. Be2 $11
) 13. Bg5 {White threatens to win material: Bg5xd8} (13. Nfg5 $5 Bd5 14. Bb5
Bxe4 15. Nxe4 $16) 13... Be7 14. Be3 Nde5 15. Nxe5 Nxe5 16. Be2 f5 17. Nc5 {
White threatens to win material: Nc5xe6. White forks: e6+b7} Bd5 18. Bd4 b6 (
18... Bf6 19. Qd2 $11) 19. Bxe5 Bxc5 20. a3 {Prevents intrusion on b4} Re8 {
Black threatens to win material: Re8xe5} 21. Bc3 Rxe2 $2 (21... Rc8 $142 $11 {
would keep Black in the game}) 22. Qxe2 $16 Qg5 23. g3 Be4 $2 (23... Qg6 $5 $16
) 24. b4 (24. Rad1 $5 {and White can already relax} Rc8 $18) 24... Bf8 25. Bd2
(25. Qc4+ Kh8 26. f3 b5 $18) 25... Qf6 26. Rac1 Re8 $2 (26... Rd8 $5 27. Bf4 g5
$16) 27. Rc7 (27. f3 Bc6 28. Qc4+ Re6 $18) 27... Qe5 (27... Kh8 28. Qc4 $18)
28. Rxa7 1-0

