{[%mdl 8192] A51: Budapest Gambit, Fajarowicz Variation} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e5 3.
d5 c6 (3... Bb4+ 4. Nd2 (4. Bd2 Bxd2+ 5. Nxd2 O-O 6. e4 d6 7. Bd3 a5 8. Ne2 Na6
9. O-O c6 10. Nc3 Nc5 11. Bc2 Bd7 12. Kh1 Qe7 13. Qe2 g6 14. f4 exf4 15. Rxf4
Nh5 16. Rf2 Qh4 17. Qe1 Rae8 18. Nf1 Qg5 {Dolezal,R (2429)-Charleshouse,G 
(2174) Teplice 2010 1/2-1/2 (32)}) 4... a5 5. g3 O-O 6. Bg2 Na6 7. Nh3 Re8 8.
O-O e4 9. Nb3 d6 10. a3 Bc5 11. Nxa5 c6 12. b4 cxd5 13. cxd5 Bb6 14. Nc4 Nxd5
15. Qxd5 Be6 16. Qb5 Bd4 17. Bg5 f6 18. Rad1 {Manolache,M (2501)-Vidal del Rio,
M (2178) Ourense 2006 1-0 (34)}) 4. Nc3 Bb4 $146 (4... cxd5 5. cxd5 d6 6. g3 g6
7. Bg2 Bg7 8. Nf3 O-O 9. O-O a6 10. a4 Nbd7 11. Nd2 Re8 12. a5 b5 13. axb6 Nxb6
14. Nb3 Qc7 15. Na5 Bd7 16. h3 Bb5 17. Re1 Nc4 18. Nxc4 Bxc4 19. Qa4 {
Hernandez,J (2300)-Remon,A (2200) Cienfuegos 1976 1-0}) 5. dxc6 Nxc6 6. Bd2 O-O
7. a3 (7. e3 Ba5 $15) 7... Bxc3 $17 8. Bxc3 d5 9. cxd5 Nxd5 10. Bd2 Bf5 11. e3
{White has a cramped position} Rc8 12. Bb5 {White is behind in development.} (
12. Ne2 Bd3 $17) 12... Qb6 13. Ba4 (13. Qb3 $5 Nf4 $1 {registering a claim to
victory} 14. Bc4 Nxg2+ 15. Kf1 Qxb3 16. Bxb3 $19) 13... Qxb2 $19 14. Ne2 Qb6 (
14... Rfd8 $142 $5 15. Qc1 Qb6 $19) 15. O-O Rfd8 16. Qe1 (16. Ng3 Nc3 $1 {
Deflection: d2} 17. Qf3 Nxa4 18. Nxf5 g6 $17) 16... Qa6 (16... Bd3 17. Bxc6
Qxc6 18. f3 $19) 17. Bb3 (17. Bxc6 Qxc6 18. f3 Qb6 $17) 17... Bd3 $19 18. Bd1
f5 19. f3 (19. a4 Qb6 $19) 19... Kh8 (19... Qb6 $142 $5 20. Rf2 Nxe3 $19) 20.
Rf2 $17 Qb6 21. Nc3 Nxc3 22. Bxc3 Qc7 (22... Qc5 23. Bb3 $17) 23. Bc2 (23. Bb3
Qe7 $15) 23... Bxc2 (23... Ne7 24. Ba5 b6 25. Bxd3 Rxd3 26. Rd2 $17) 24. Rxc2
Qf7 25. f4 (25. Rac1 Qe6 $17) 25... exf4 26. exf4 Re8 {Black threatens to win
material: Re8xe1} (26... Nd4 $142 27. Rd2 Re8 $17) 27. Qg3 $4 (27. Re2 Rxe2 28.
Qxe2 Qe7 $17) 27... Kg8 $4 {hands over the advantage to the opponent} (27...
Nd4 $142 $1 {and Black wins} 28. Bxd4 Rxc2 $19) 28. Rac1 Re7 29. Bb2 Rce8 30.
Rc5 g6 (30... Re3 $142 $5 31. Rxf5 Rxg3 32. Rxf7 Rxg2+ 33. Kxg2 Kxf7 $17) 31.
Qc3 $11 {White has a mate threat} Kf8 32. a4 Re4 {Black threatens to win
material: Re4xa4. Black forks: a4+f4} 33. Ba3 Kg8 34. Bb2 (34. Rxc6 bxc6 35.
Bb2 Kf8 $11) 34... Kf8 $4 {Black is ruining his position} (34... Nd4 $142 35.
Qxd4 Rxd4 36. Bxd4 Qd7 $17) 35. Ba3 $4 {White lets it slip away} (35. Rb5 Re3
36. Qh8+ Qg8 37. Qf6+ Qf7 38. Qxf7+ Kxf7 39. Rxb7+ R8e7 40. Rxe7+ Nxe7 $11)
35... Kg8 {Twofold repetition} 36. Bb2 Kf8 1/2-1/2

