Grabarczyk,B (2441)-Macieja,B (2629) Opole 2007 0-1 (40)}) 8. cxd4 Ba7 9. Re1
d6 $146 {Prevents intrusion on e5} (9... b5 10. Bb3 d6 11. h3 Na5 12. Bc2 Bb7
13. Bg5 h6 14. Bh4 Re8 {1/2-1/2 (14) Laszlo,J (2280)-Mester,G (2255) Debrecen
1994}) 10. h3 {Controls g4} d5 11. e5 {White gets more space} Ne4 12. Bc2 {
White threatens to win material: Bc2xe4} f5 {White has a new protected passed
pawn: e5} 13. Nc3 Be6 {Blocks the pawn on e5} 14. Bb3 Ne7 (14... h6 15. a3 $11)
15. Be3 (15. Nxe4 $5 fxe4 16. Ng5 $16) 15... c6 {Secures b5} 16. Ng5 {White
threatens to win material: Ng5xe6} (16. a4 h6 $11) 16... Qd7 (16... Nxg5 17.
Bxg5 f4 18. Qd2 $15) 17. Ne2 {White has an active position} (17. Nxe6 Qxe6 18.
Ne2 Ng6 $14) 17... Ng6 (17... f4 $5 18. Bxf4 Rxf4 19. Nxe6 Rxf2 $11) 18. Nxe6
$14 Qxe6 19. Nf4 (19. f3 $5 f4 20. fxe4 fxe3 21. Qd3 $14) 19... Nxf4 $11 20.
Bxf4 g5 (20... Qe7 21. Qd3 $11) 21. Bc1 (21. Bh2 Rae8 $16) 21... Qg6 22. f3 {
White threatens to win material: f3xe4} Ng3 23. Bc2 h6 (23... Qh6 $142 $14) 24.
e6 $4 {weakening the position} (24. Kh2 $142 Nh5 25. Rf1 $16) 24... Rae8 $17
25. f4 $2 (25. Be3 $142 $17) 25... Rxe6 $19 26. Be3 $2 (26. Kh2 Rxe1 27. Qxe1
$19) 26... Rfe8 27. Bf2 Rxe1+ 28. Bxe1 Bxd4+ $1 {Decoy: d4} 29. Bf2 (29. Qxd4
Ne2+ {Decoy Double attack}) 29... Bxf2+ 30. Kxf2 gxf4 31. Qd4 (31. Kg1 Ne2+ 32.
Kf1 f3 33. g4 Qd6 34. Be4 Qh2 35. Ke1 Nd4 36. Qd3 Rxe4+ 37. Qxe4 fxe4 38. Kf1
Qg2+ 39. Ke1 Qe2#) 31... Ne4+ (31... Re2+ 32. Kg1 f3 33. Qf2 Rxf2 34. Kxf2 Ne4+
35. Bxe4 Qxg2+ 36. Ke3 fxe4 37. h4 f2 38. Rc1 Qf3+ 39. Kd4 f1=Q 40. Rxf1 Qxf1
41. b3 b6 42. Ke5 e3 43. Kd6 e2 44. h5 e1=Q 45. Kxc6 Qb5+ 46. Kb7 Qe7+ 47. Kc8
Qbe8#) 32. Kg1 (32. Bxe4 fxe4 33. b3 e3+ 34. Kg1 Qg3 35. Qxf4 Qxf4 36. Rf1 Qh4
37. Kh1 e2 38. Rg1 e1=Q 39. b4 Qxg1+ 40. Kxg1 Qg3 41. Kh1 Re1#) 32... f3 (32...
