{[%mdl 8192] E97: King's Indian: Classical Main Line (6...e5 7 0-0 Nc6): 8 Be3
and 8 d5 Ne7, not 9 Ne1} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4. e4 d6 5. Nf3 O-O 6.
Be2 e5 7. O-O Nc6 8. d5 Ne7 9. b4 a5 10. Ba3 axb4 11. Bxb4 Bd7 $146 (11... b6
12. a4 Bd7 (12... Ne8 13. Nb5 (13. a5 c5 14. dxc6 bxa5 (14... Nxc6 15. Ba3 Nxa5
16. Nb5 Nb7 17. Bb4 Rxa1 18. Qxa1 Nc5 19. Bxc5 bxc5 20. Qa8 Nc7 21. Qc6 Nxb5
22. cxb5 Qd7 23. Rd1 Rd8 24. Qb6 Bf6 25. Nd2 Qb7 26. Qxb7 Bxb7 27. Nc4 Bxe4 28.
Rxd6 Rxd6 29. Nxd6 {Nutu Gajic,D (2350)-Jelica,M (2165) Nova Gorica 1992 1/2-1/
2 (40)}) 15. c7 Qxc7 16. Nd5 Nxd5 17. cxd5 Nf6 18. Bd3 Bf5 19. Rc1 Qb8 20. Ba3
Bxe4 21. Bxe4 Nxe4 22. Rc6 a4 23. Nd2 Nxd2 24. Qxd2 Rd8 25. Rfc1 e4 26. Rc7 Qb3
27. Qf4 Qxd5 {Finegold,B (2490)-Har Zvi,R (2425) Groningen 1992 0-1 (40)})
13... f5 14. a5 (14. Nd2 Kh8 15. Bf3 Ng8 16. a5 bxa5 17. Rxa5 Rxa5 18. Bxa5
Ngf6 19. Qc2 Bd7 20. Rb1 Qa8 21. Bxc7 Nxc7 22. Nxc7 Qc8 23. Nb5 Qc5 24. Nb3 Qb6
25. Nc3 Rc8 26. c5 dxc5 27. Nd2 Qa6 28. Be2 c4 {Veingold,A (2425)-Maki,V (2420)
Finland 1996 1/2-1/2 (41)}) 14... fxe4 15. Nd2 c5 16. dxc6 Nxc6 17. Bc3 bxa5
18. Nxe4 Be6 19. Nexd6 Nxd6 20. Nxd6 Nd4 21. c5 Nb3 22. Bf3 Ra7 23. Bd5 Nxc5
24. Bxe6+ Nxe6 25. Qd5 Qe7 26. Bxe5 Bxe5 27. Qxe5 {Anand,V (2725)-Shirov,A 
(2690) Monte Carlo 1996 1/2-1/2 (48)}) 13. a5 bxa5 14. Bxa5 Ne8 15. Nd2 f5 16.
c5 dxc5 17. Nb3 c4 18. Nd2 Nd6 19. Nxc4 Nec8 20. Qb3 Ra7 21. Qb4 Nxc4 22. Bxc4
Nd6 23. Ra2 Kh8 24. Rfa1 Qg5 25. Qc5 Rfa8 26. Bxc7 {Panczyk,K (2380)-Nicevski,
R (2355) Polanica Zdroj 1982 0-1 (33)}) 12. c5 {White threatens to win
material: c5xd6} Ne8 13. a4 f5 {Black has a cramped position} 14. Ng5 fxe4 15.
Ncxe4 Nf5 16. Bg4 {White has a very active position} (16. Bc4 Nd4 $16) 16...
Nd4 {An ideal square for the black knight.} (16... Qe7 17. Re1 $14) 17. cxd6 (
17. Be6+ Kh8 $16) 17... cxd6 (17... Nxd6 $5 {must definitely be considered} 18.
Bxd7 Qxd7 $16) 18. Be6+ $16 Bxe6 19. Nxe6 Nxe6 20. dxe6 Rf4 21. Rb1 (21. Qd5
Qe7 22. a5 h6 $18) 21... Rxe4 22. e7 Qxe7 23. Qd5+ Kh8 (23... Qf7 $5 24. Qxe4
d5 $16) 24. Qxe4 Nf6 25. Qc2 Qd7 26. Rfd1 Bf8 $2 (26... d5 $5 $16) 27. a5 $18
Rc8 (27... Rd8 28. Ba3 $18) 28. Qb3 Rc6 $2 (28... Rc7 $142 $18) 29. Be1 Rc7 (
29... Qd8 $18 {cannot undo what has already been done}) 30. f3 (30. Rdc1 {
keeps an even firmer grip} Rxc1 31. Rxc1 h6 $18) 30... Nh5 $2 (30... Qe8 31.
Bh4 Nh5 32. Rdc1 $18) 31. g3 (31. Rdc1 $142 $18 {makes it even easier for White
}) 31... Qc6 $4 {terrible, but what else could Black do to save the game?} (
31... Ng7 32. Rdc1 Rxc1 33. Rxc1 $18) 32. Bf2 (32. Rdc1 $142 {and the rest is
a matter of technique} Qxc1 33. Rxc1 Rxc1 34. Qf7 $18) 32... Kg7 $6 {puts up
no fight} (32... Ng7 $18) 33. Qd5 Qc2 (33... Qa6 {a last effort to resist the
inevitable} 34. Rdc1 Rd7 $18) 34. Rxb7 Rxb7 (34... Nf6 {praying for a miracle}
35. Qd3 Qxf2+ 36. Kxf2 Rxb7 $18) 35. Qxb7+ (35. Qxb7+ Kf6 36. Re1 Nxg3 37. hxg3
$18) 1-0

