{[%mdl 8192] B04: Alekhine's Defence: 4 Nf3} 1. e4 Nf6 2. e5 Nd5 3. d4 d6 4.
Nf3 dxe5 5. dxe5 Bf5 6. Bc4 {White threatens to win material: Bc4xd5} (6. Nd4
Bg6 7. e6 c6 8. Bd3 Qd6 9. exf7+ Bxf7 10. O-O Nd7 11. Re1 Nc5 12. Na3 Qf6 13.
Nc4 Nxd3 14. Qxd3 Nb4 15. Qc3 Nxc2 16. Bg5 Qxd4 17. Qxd4 Nxd4 18. Nd6+ Kd7 19.
Nxf7 Rg8 20. Rad1 c5 {Martin Del Campo C,R (2465)-Garcia Martinez,S (2415)
Havana 1990 1-0 (39)}) 6... c6 $146 {Black is behind in developement. Black's
piece can't move: f8} (6... e6 7. Qe2 (7. Bg5 Qd7 8. Qe2 h6 9. Bd2 Nc6 10. Bb3
g5 11. h3 Bb4 12. Nc3 Nxc3 13. Bxc3 Bxc3+ 14. bxc3 g4 15. hxg4 Bxg4 16. Ba4 Qd5
17. Rd1 Bxf3 18. gxf3 Qc5 19. Qe3 Qa5 20. Bxc6+ bxc6 21. Qd4 Qd5 {Nicolini,A 
(2154)-Borik,J (2198) Slovakia 2012 1-0 (50)}) 7... c6 8. O-O Bg4 9. Bb3 Nd7
10. c4 Ne7 11. Bf4 Ng6 12. Bg3 Bxf3 13. Qxf3 Ndxe5 14. Qh5 Nd7 15. Nc3 {
1/2-1/2 (15) Stehno,P (2301)-Turner,J (2344) Marianske Lazne 2004}) 7. O-O e6 {
Consolidates d5} 8. Bb3 {White has an active position} Nd7 9. Nbd2 Qc7 10. Re1
Be7 11. Nf1 O-O-O 12. a4 (12. Bd2 Kb8 $15) 12... h5 (12... Nb4 $5 $17) 13. Bxd5
cxd5 14. c3 {Consolidates b4} Bg4 15. Qd4 (15. N1d2 Nxe5 {Deflection: f3} 16.
Rxe5 Qxe5 17. Nxe5 Bxd1 18. Nxf7 g5 $15) 15... Bxf3 $17 16. gxf3 Bc5 17. Qf4
Rdf8 18. b4 Be7 19. Qd4 {White threatens to win material: Qd4xa7} Kb8 20. Be3
Qb6 21. Nd2 Qxd4 {Black forks: c3+e5} 22. Bxd4 {The bishop likes it on d4} g5
23. a5 {White gains space} Rfg8 {[%cal Yg5g4] Black intends g4} 24. Reb1 (24.
Nb3 Nf8 $15) 24... g4 {Black wins space} 25. f4 h4 (25... Nf8 $5 $17) 26. c4
$11 dxc4 27. Nxc4 g3 28. Nd6 (28. Rd1 Rg4 29. Be3 Nf8 $16) 28... gxh2+ {
White is in double check} (28... f6 29. exf6 Bxf6 30. Rd1 $11) 29. Kxh2 $11
Bxd6 (29... Rg4 $5 {is noteworthy} 30. Be3 Bxd6 31. exd6 Nf6 $11) 30. exd6 $16
{White has a new passed pawn: d6. Black has a new passed pawn: h4} Rh5 31. Rg1
{White has a mate threat} Rc8 (31... Rd8 $14) 32. Rac1 (32. a6 $142 $5 Rb5 33.
axb7 Rxb7 34. Kh3 $16) 32... Rxc1 $11 33. Rxc1 {White has a king attack} Rd5 {
Black threatens to win material: Rd5xd4. Black forks: d4+d6} 34. Rg1 {White
has a mate threat} b6 {Black threatens to win material: b6xa5} 35. a6 {White
has a mate threat} (35. Be5 $142 bxa5 36. bxa5 Rxa5 37. Rg7 $11) 35... Ka8 $4 {
forfeits the clear win} (35... Rxd6 $142 {would hold out} 36. Rg8+ Kc7 $17) 36.
Rg8+ Nb8 37. Be5 (37. Be5 f6 38. Bxf6 Rd2 39. Be5 Rxf2+ 40. Kh3 Rf3+ 41. Kxh4
Rh3+ 42. Kxh3 b5 43. Rxb8+ Kxb8 44. d7+ Ka8 45. d8=Q#) 1-0

