{[%mdl 8192] B13: Caro-Kann: Exchange Variation and Panov-Botvinnik Attack} 1.
e4 c6 2. c3 d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. d4 Nc6 6. Bb5 (6. Bf4 g6 7. Be2 Bg7
8. O-O O-O 9. Nbd2 Nh5 10. Be3 Qd6 11. Re1 f5 12. Nb3 f4 13. Bd2 Kh8 14. Bd3
Bg4 15. Be2 Rae8 16. Ng5 Bxe2 17. Rxe2 e5 18. dxe5 Nxe5 19. Nd4 h6 20. Ngf3
Nxf3+ {Turov,M (2490)-Burmakin,V (2530) Moscow 1994 1/2-1/2 (42)}) (6. Ne5 g6
7. Bb5 Bd7 8. Qb3 a6 9. Bd3 Na5 10. Qd1 Bg7 11. Nd2 O-O 12. h4 Nc6 13. f4 Bf5
14. Be2 h5 15. Nf1 Ne4 16. g4 hxg4 17. Bxg4 Qc8 18. Ne3 Bxg4 19. N5xg4 e6 20.
Qf3 f5 {Mona,K (2154)-Wageih,K (2316) Cairo 2014 0-1 (42)}) 6... a6 $146 {
Black threatens to win material: a6xb5} (6... Qb6 7. Qb3 Bd7 8. O-O e6 9. Bf4
Na5 10. Bxd7+ Nxd7 11. Qc2 Bd6 12. Bxd6 Qxd6 13. Nbd2 Rc8 14. Qd3 O-O 15. Ng5
Nf6 16. Rae1 Nc4 17. Nxc4 Rxc4 18. f4 g6 19. Qh3 Kg7 20. Re3 b5 21. Qh4 {
James,R (2225)-Arkell,K (2506) Paington 2008 0-1 (40)}) 7. Bd3 Bg4 8. h3 {
White threatens to win material: h3xg4} Bh5 9. O-O e6 {Secures f5} 10. Bg5 Be7
11. Nbd2 O-O 12. Qc2 Bg6 13. Bxg6 hxg6 14. Rfe1 Rc8 15. Qd3 Re8 16. Rac1 Qa5
17. a3 {Prevents intrusion on b4} Nh7 {Black threatens to win material: Nh7xg5}
18. Bf4 Qd8 19. Bg3 Bd6 20. Ne5 Nxe5 21. Bxe5 Be7 22. Nf3 Ng5 23. Nh2 Ne4 24.
f3 {White threatens to win material: f3xe4} Nd6 25. Ng4 Nc4 {Black threatens
to win material: Nc4xb2} 26. Rc2 Bd6 27. Bxd6 Nxd6 28. Rce2 Nc4 29. Ne3 Qd7 30.
Nxc4 dxc4 31. Qe4 Qb5 32. Qc2 Rcd8 33. Re5 {White threatens to win material:
Re5xb5} Rd5 34. f4 Red8 35. R1e2 Qb6 36. Kh2 Qc7 37. g3 b5 38. Qb1 Qb7 39. Qe1
a5 40. g4 b4 41. axb4 axb4 42. Rxd5 {White has a mate threat} Rxd5 43. Re5 Rxe5
44. dxe5 bxc3 45. bxc3 {A queen endgame occured.} Qf3 {Black threatens to win
material: Qf3xf4} 46. Qd2 Kh7 47. Qd4 {White threatens to win material: Qd4xc4}
(47. g5 $5 $11 {must be considered}) 47... Qd3 $15 48. Qf2 f6 (48... g5 $5 {
is worth consideration} 49. fxg5 Qxc3 50. Qxf7 Qd2+ 51. Kg1 Qxg5 52. Qxe6 c3
$15) 49. Qh4+ $11 Kg8 50. exf6 Qd2+ {Black forks: f4} 51. Kg1 Qxf4 52. fxg7 {
White has a mate threat} Kxg7 {Black has a new passed pawn: e6.} 53. Qe7+ {
White forks: e6} Qf7 $4 {a weak move, ruining a winning position} (53... Kh8
54. Qe8+ Kg7 55. Qe7+ Kh8 56. Qe8+ Kg7 57. Qe7+ $11) 54. Qc5 {White threatens
to win material: Qc5xc4} (54. Qxf7+ $142 {and White has prevailed} Kxf7 55. h4
$18) 54... Qf4 $4 {ruins a very nice position} (54... Qf3 55. Qe7+ Kh6 56. Qh4+
Kg7 57. Qe7+ Kh6 58. Qh4+ Kg7 59. Qe7+ $11) 55. Qe7+ {Twofold repetition} Qf7
56. Qc5 Qf4 1/2-1/2

